22/06/2007
BUCHAREST, Romania -- A heat wave across the Balkans is blamed for at least 22 deaths, 19 in Romania alone. Temperatures over 35 degrees Celsius have prompted officials to start distributing bottles of cold water in some areas. In Albania, temperatures nearing 40 degrees Celsius are blamed for three more deaths in the southern city of Elbasan. Even higher temperatures are forecast for the weeks ahead. (Mediafax, A1 TV, bTV, AFP - 21/06/07)
